cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR

This paper is about improving dynamic symbolic execution, which is a technique used in software engineering to automatically test programs. The paper focuses on the search heuristic used in dynamic symbolic execution, which is a key challenge in achieving high code coverage in a limited time budget. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper presents an algorithm for finding an optimal heuristic, which involves machine learning techniques, so it could also fit in the categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates its technique in terms of bug-finding, which could also make it relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
